hement. Die Beiträger*innen bringen aus historischer, systematischer, normativer und empirischer Perspektive diesen Diskurs voran. Damit liefern sie unverzichtbare Grundlagen für alle, die für die Auswahl und Didaktisierung religionsunterrichtlicher Inhalte in Theorie und Praxis verantwortlich sind.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aBildung. 4aBildungsforschung. 4aBildungstheorie. 4aDidaktik. 4aLehrplan. 4aReligion. 4aReligionspädagogik. 4aReligionswissenschaft. 4aSchule. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh  aDidactics.  aEducation.  aEducational Research.  aReligion.  aReligious Studies.  aSchool.  aTheory of Education.1 aBucher, Georg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBöhringer, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaspary, Christiane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDomsgen, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFricke, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGennerich, Carsten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGojny, Tanja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGojny, Tanja, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGrasser, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrätz, Sebastian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuttenberger, Gudrun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHamilton, Nadine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeller, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4htt